fields.summary: [Python] "could not run mc" error in test_fs.py

comments.body: I think your mc version is too old.  It looks like the `mc alias set` command was added in August 2020 and you are running the July 2019 version.
We can probably add a minimum version check in the python test and skip if it's too old.

Ok, I upgraded mc. But now I get a different error:
{code}
________________________________________________ ERROR at setup of test_s3fs_limited_permissions_create_bucket _________________________________________________
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/home/antoine/arrow/dev/python/pyarrow/tests/test_fs.py", line 397, in limited_s3_user
    if not _configure_limited_user(tempdir, address, access_key, secret_key):
  File "/home/antoine/arrow/dev/python/pyarrow/tests/test_fs.py", line 373, in _configure_limited_user
    _run_mc_command(mcdir, 'admin', 'policy', 'add',
  File "/home/antoine/arrow/dev/python/pyarrow/tests/test_fs.py", line 336, in _run_mc_command
    raise ChildProcessError("Could not run mc")
ChildProcessError: Could not run mc
-------------------------------------------------------------------- Captured stdout setup ---------------------------------------------------------------------
Cmd: mc -C /tmp/tmpwztknhnm/mc alias set myminio http://localhost:36975 arrow apachearrow
  Return: 1
  Stdout: mc: Configuration written to `/tmp/tmpwztknhnm/mc/config.json`. Please update your access credentials.
mc: Successfully created `/tmp/tmpwztknhnm/mc/share`.
mc: Initialized share uploads `/tmp/tmpwztknhnm/mc/share/uploads.json` file.
mc: Initialized share downloads `/tmp/tmpwztknhnm/mc/share/downloads.json` file.

  Stderr: mc: <ERROR> Unable to initialize new alias from the provided credentials. Get "http://localhost:36975/probe-bucket-sign-542otzhvjmgy/?location=": dial tcp 127.0.0.1:36975: connect: connection refused.

Attempting encryption of all config, IAM users and policies on MinIO backend
Cmd: mc -C /tmp/tmpwztknhnm/mc alias set myminio http://localhost:36975 arrow apachearrow
  Return: 0
  Stdout: Added `myminio` successfully.

  Stderr: 
Cmd: mc -C /tmp/tmpwztknhnm/mc admin policy add myminio/ no-create-buckets /tmp/tmpwztknhnm/limited-buckets-policy.json
  Return: 1
  Stdout: 
  Stderr: mc: <ERROR> Unable to add new policy. Unexpected client 'admin' API version found 'v3', expected 'v2', please downgrade the client to older releases.

{code}
Turns out the minio server was too old as well :-) Now it works fine. Thank you!
Weston is adding a version check to avoid this in the future.
